  "description": "Language-neutral UI text strings for the picker. Edit these to change the search prompt, status bar, and help screen without touching code. {count} is substituted with the live match count. Keep lines within the rendered content width (spec/layout.json) or they are truncated. Consumed by both the Zig app and the Go mojigo port. help_lines is the default help page (query starts with '?'); help_lines_more is the second page shown when the query starts with '??' and documents the e:/t: width filters. cursor_left/cursor_right are the cursor box drawn around the focused emoji (default ⌜ ⌟; try [ ], ⟨ ⟩, ▏ ▕ — each must be one display cell). multi_select_mark is the glyph prefixed to emojis picked in multi-select mode — keep it a single display cell wide (e.g. ✓ ✔ · • ▸) so the 4-column grid stays aligned. When multi_select_mark is \"\" the mark is dropped and picked cells are instead highlighted with multi_select_bg (a color name like green/blue or a 0-255 palette index). Rebuild (zig build) after editing since specs are embedded at compile time.",
  "focus_lost_runtime_lines": [
    "🕵️ Picker unfocused.",
    "   Click or switch window",
    "   to focus!"
  ],
  "focus_lost_startup_lines": [
